12 b. A final maturity of ten years or less;
13 (c) Money market investments; or
14 (d) Any combination of investments described in paragraphs (a) to (c) of this
15 subdivision; and
16 (2) Shall invest the remaining percentage of any available funds not invested as
17 allowed under subdivision (1) of this subsection into any investment in which the state
18 treasurer is allowed to invest.
19 2. The provisions of this section shall only apply if the hospital:
20 (1) Receives less than [one] three percent of its annual revenues from municipal,
21 county, or state taxes; and
22 (2) Receives less than [one] three percent of its annual revenue from appropriated
23 funds from the municipality in which such hospital is located.
